{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "e47b1c10-0000-4a00-9000-eatzy0000001",
    "name": "Eatzy - Food Delivery API",
    "description": "End-to-end collection for the Eatzy microservice backend, all through the gateway (http://localhost:3000).\n\nUsage: run the requests top-to-bottom. The Auth requests capture per-role tokens (ownerToken / customerToken / driverToken) and Create requests capture ids (restaurantId, menuId, orderId, paymentId, deliveryId, ...) into collection variables, so later requests just work.\n\nFor a full happy-path Collection Run, run: Auth -> Restaurants -> Restaurant Owner -> Menu -> Reviews -> Orders -> Payments -> Delivery -> Notifications. The DELETE requests are destructive - run them last (the Cleanup folder) or skip them.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
